<p>I have a datepicker which I only want the user to be able to select a month and year.</p>  <p>The user should only be able to select up to a year from todays date.  I have this working but I cant seem to get only the months displaying.</p>  <p><strong>HTML</strong></p>  <pre><code>&lt;div class="form-groups"&gt;     &lt;div class="col-sm-12"&gt;         &lt;div class="input-group"&gt;             &lt;input type="text" name="idTourDateDetails" id="idTourDateDetails" class="form-control clsDatePicker"&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;     &lt;/div&gt; &lt;/div&gt; </code></pre>  <p><strong>Script</strong></p>  <pre><code>&lt;script type="text/javascript"&gt;         $('#idTourDateDetails').datepicker({         format: "mm-yyyy",         startMode: "months",          minViewMode: "months",         changeMonth: true,         changeYear: true,         minDate: '0d',         maxDate: '1y'     }); &lt;/script&gt; </code></pre>  <p>I tried adding <code>data-date-format="mm-yyyy"</code> to the <code>input</code> but it didn't work.</p>  <p>See working <a href="http://jsfiddle.net/RQgCW/103/" rel="nofollow">fiddle</a></p>  <p>I do not want to just hide the calendar, I want the dates to display the months instead.  Other suggestion below only hide the calendar.</p>  <p>This <a href="http://jsfiddle.net/RWY2X/2/" rel="nofollow">fiddle</a> is what I'm after but I can't get it working as when I put the HTML and the JQuery into my solution, I get the dates still displayed.</p>